  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Overview:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Since we depend on SCR to wake the system from Standby mode, it is important to make sure the SCR code is properly running in XC800 CPU"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Features of SCR WDT:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "16 bit WDT Timer",
        "Programmable Window boundary",
        "Can run in 70 kHz Clock"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The Watchdog Timer maintains a counter which must be refreshed or cleared periodically. Otherwise, the counter will overflow and the watchdog reset will be asserted"
    },
    {
      "type": "panel",
      "panel_type": "info",
      "title": "",
      "content": "The assertion of the reset could be disabled by setting bit RSTCON.WDTRSTEN. The occurrence of a WDT reset is indicated by the bit WDTRST in RSTST register"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In the SCR, it is possible to wake-up the main controller from standby mode when the WDT overflow event happened by setting bit STDBYWKP.WDTWKSEL to 1 ."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "NMI"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Before SCR WDT triggers the Reset, NMI will be triggered where we can log some critical information to Error Memory"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/SCR%20-%20Watch%20Dog/image2022-8-5_12-7-6.png?api=v2",
