    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Programmable window boundary"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The WDT has a “programmable window boundary”, which disallows any refresh during the WDT’s count-up. A refresh during this window-boundary constitutes an invalid access to the WDT and causes the WDT to activate WDTRST"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This feature can be enabled by WINBEN bit in Watchdog Timer Control Register"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/SCR%20-%20Watch%20Dog/image2022-8-5_12-12-5.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
